  <summary>A team of U.S. government agents is sent to investigate the bombing of an American facility in the Middle East.</summary>
  <reviews>
    <item index="0">
      <text>The Kingdom works as an exotic action thriller, but its politics are so choked on checks and balances it cancels itself out.</text>
      <source>CNN.com</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.cnn.com/2007/SHOWBIZ/Movies/09/28/review.kingdom/index.html</link>
      <author>Tom Charity</author>
    </item>
    <item index="1">
      <text>When it's got the pedal to the metal, which is a substantial fraction of the running time, The Kingdom delivers the goods.</text>
      <source>Film.com</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.filmfreak.be/index.php?module=filmfreak&amp;func=viewpub&amp;tid=9&amp;pid=406&amp;title=The.Kingdom</link>
      <author>Jonathan F. Richards</author>
    </item>
    <item index="2">
      <text>A terrifically stupid film. Dumb, dumb, dumb.</text>
      <source>Time Out</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.timeout.com/film/reviews/84341/the-kingdom.html</link>
      <author>Dave Calhoun</author>
    </item>
    <item index="3">
      <text>Everything moves so much and so fast that the movie seems both gutsy and brainy. But the main strategy is to keep viewers' pulses racing so they concentrate on the action, not the message.</text>
      <source>TIME Magazine</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.time.com/time/arts/article/0,8599,1666758,00.html</link>
      <author>Richard Corliss</author>
    </item>
    <item index="4">
      <text>The Kingdom comes down to a police procedural, and one whose procedures prove none too interesting.</text>
      <source>Wall Street Journal</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://online.wsj.com/article/SB119093399274741863.html?mod=2_1168_1</link>
      <author>Joe Morgenstern</author>
    </item>
    <item index="5">
      <text>The Kingdom may be the most potent counter-programming of the year, even though it has no patience with such sissy-pants concerns.</text>
      <source>Toronto Star</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.thestar.com/entertainment/article/261407</link>
      <author>Peter Howell</author>
    </item>
    <item index="6">
      <text>The movie pretends to be a dramatic exploration of the gulf of mutual suspicion that has grown from the oil alliance between the United States and Saudi Arabia. In the most superficial way imaginable, it does that.</text>
      <source>San Jose Mercury News</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.mercurynews.com/movies/ci_7018003</link>
      <author>Bruce Newman</author>
    </item>
    <item index="7">
      <text>After outdoing himself in the opening sequence, director Peter Berg, who appears briefly as an FBI honcho, overdoes everything that follows.</text>
      <source>San Francisco Chronicle</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=/c/a/2007/09/28/DDBHSEIDK.DTL&amp;type=movies</link>
      <author>Mick LaSalle</author>
    </item>
    <item index="8">
      <text>A xenophobic, overblown, revenge-driven action thriller that exports the Rambo mentality to the contemporary Middle East.</text>
      <source>New York Post</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.nypost.com/seven/09282007/entertainment/movies/the_king_dumb.htm</link>
      <author>Lou Lumenick</author>
    </item>
    <item index="9">
      <text>Does it feel real? No. Is it fun? Yes. Will it win the war? Hey, I see light at the end of the tunnel.</text>
      <source>New York Daily News</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/2007/09/28/2007-09-28_blast_action_heroes_take_saudi_power_tri.html</link>
      <author>Jack Mathews</author>
    </item>
    <item index="10">
      <text>It wants us to feel as if we're watching something relevant when what's really going on is a slick excuse for efficient mayhem that's not half as smart as it would like to be.</text>
      <source>Los Angeles Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.calendarlive.com/movies/turan/cl-et-kingdom28sep28,0,6634156.story</link>
      <author>Kenneth Turan</author>
    </item>
